To Configure Plymouth Use sudo nano /etc/default/grub then GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT="quiet splash" ctrl x then y then enter then sudo update-grub
Then sudo nano /usr/share/plymouth/themes/ubuntu-text/ubuntu-text.plymouth Then Change title=Ubuntu 24.04 to title=Triaxis GNU/Linux Ctrl X Y Enter Then sudo update-initramfs -u
Then Reboot Or sudo plymouthd then sudo plymouth --show-splash
If You Want More Extra Themes
Command
sudo apt update
sudo apt install plymouth-themes
If you want spinner theme
sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/Triaxis-logo.png /usr/share/plymouth/themes/spinner/watermark.png
sudo update-initramfs -u
if you want to change bgrt fallback here
sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/triaxis-logo.png /usr/share/plymouth/themes/spinner/bgrt-fallback.png
sudo update-initramfs -u
If you want to set a theme you want
sudo update-alternatives --config default.plymouth
/usr/share/plymouth/themes/yourtheme/yourtheme.plymouth
Example
/usr/share/plymouth/themes/spinner/spinner.plymouth
